awing of Saint George slaying the dragon. </p><p>  Fol. 1r: In later hand, in ball point pen, "This homily belongs to Liqä Diyaqon Täšomä." </p><p>  Fols. 9r, 13v, 14r, 21r, 24r, passim: The original owner's name has been erased and replaced with Zäyohannəs and Məskabä Dəngəl at the end of every homily and miracle </p><p>  Fol. 14v: The second owners' names have been erased and replaced with Kənfä Mika'el. </p><p>  Fol. 25r: The second owners' names have been erased and replaced with Wäldä Giyorgis. </p><p>  Fols. 65r, 68v: The scribe's name is mentioned, Efrem. </p><p> Gift of Bruce Willsie, Princeton Class of 1986.</p><p>In another hand.</p><p>How the Archangel Gabriel announced the Virgin Mary when she was spinning silk yarn for the temple.</p><p>In another hand, fitted around the bottom of the existing text.</p><p>In another hand, from another manuscript.</p><!--BIBLIOGRAPHY--><p>References: See references listed in manuscript no. 21.</p></summary><msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus>Located on folio 3r-66r.</locus><title>Homily [in Honor] of [the Archangel] Michael</title><date cert="low" notBefore="1770" notAfter="1830">circa 1770-1830</date></msItem><msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus>Located on folio 66r.</locus><title>Magical Prayer Against Snakes</title><date cert="low" notBefore="1770" notAfter="1830">circa 1770-1830</date></msItem><msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus>Located on folio 67r-68v.</locus><title>First Miracle of Mary</title><date cert="low" notBefore="1770" notAfter="1830">circa 1770-1830</date></msItem><msItem xml:id="ms_i4"><locus>Located on folio 68v-69v.</locus><title>Magical Prayer Against Eye Disease and the Protection of Cattle</title><date cert="low" notBefore="1770" notAfter="1830">circa 1770-1830</date></msItem><msItem xml:id="ms_i5"><locus>Located on folio 68v-69v.</locus><title>First Folio of a Gospel of John</title><date cert="low" notBefore="1770" notAfter="1830">circa 1770-1830</date></msItem><msItem xml:id="ms_i6"><locus>Located on folio 3r-9r.</l